14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 840-2.31 of Title 74, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. No public employee, including an employee of a state agency,
19 a political subdivision, or a school district, whose salary or wages
20 are paid with taxpayer dollars may speak on or participate in a
21 matter of public concern deemed a matter of larger societal
22 significance or importance, either as an individual or as an
23 organized form of protest, during the employee’s normal work hours;
24 provided, a public employee is authorized to engage in such conduct
