1 duri ng normal work hours if the employee uses annual leave and the
2 actions of the employee will not create an undue burden on the
3 employer’s interests in an efficient, disruptive-free workplace.
4 B. In no event shall a public employee use assets or equipment
5 owned by the state, a political subdivision, or a school district
6 for any purpose, other than at school events or for express purposes
7 outlined in the employee’s job description, for conduct pursuant to
8 subsection A of this section, including, but not limited to:
9 1. Computer equipment, including equipment that facilitates the
10 use of email, text messaging, or social media from any state-owned,
11 -leased, or -funded devices;
12 2. Transportation equipment, including any vehicles, school
13 buses, trailers, or other modes of transportation; or
14 3. Any other materials, including food, sound equipment, or
15 material utilizing the employer emblem, insignia, or symbol.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
17 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
18 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
19 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
20 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
